            "answer_text": "Yes, before Europeans ever stepped foot in North America. For instance the Comanches were at war with or had skirmishes against the following at some point (other tribes, people groups): Coahuiltecan, Chisos, Jano, Manso, Apaches, Utes, Lakotas, Cheyenne, Arikara Pawnees, Kansa, Osage, Kiowa The French The Spanish Americans Mexico In at least one case it was killing 10 members of a another group for stealing horses from them after they stole horses from that group. You have to understand that at their height the Comanches had 10k tribes members and wanted to exclusively own 10% of the lands west of the Mississippi. In their system it was simply impossible to sustain themselves. They could never of had say factories or farms which would have sustained millions of people. Like other people have pointed out atrocities are common to man. The land we call China was at one point many tribes but one THE CHIN killed off or chased away all of the others. Etcetera, etcetera, ",
