            "answer_text": "North American Indigenous Warfare and Ritual Violence In North America we have to deal with archaeological artifacts and interpretations, along with the verbal traditions of the Native American tribes. If we slide down to the Yucat\u00e1n, we don\u2019t need to base everything on soft records and interpretations. The maya had a very complete written language and many of the Mayan inscriptions record details of their frequent wars between the various Mayan city states and the gruesome aftermaths. It would appear that perhaps the idyllic and noble savage is just one more of those myths of \u201cpolitically correct\u201d science! ",
