            "answer_text": "there was only one known massacre prior to columbus getting lost, bringing judeo-christian genocidal colonialism , smallox and syphilis to turtle island. , the crow creek massacre in south dakota in the early 14th century. List of Indian massacres - Wikipedia Like any other people, there were rogues who were brigands, but for the most part, intertribal warfare was more akin to a polo match, winning victory by \u201ccounting coup\u201d, rather than a fight to the death. Encyclopedia of the Great Plains Things changed drastically in post-columbian times, because rival tribes would scout for the colonial armies. The sioux nations may never have been defeated if their enemies didn\u2019t help the army, scouting out their winter camps. ",
